Anaconda Notes

conda upgrade conda
conda upgrade --all

conda install numpy scipy pandas

conda create -n env_name list of packages
conda create -n my_env numpy.

conda create -n py3 python=3 
source activate my_env
source deactivate

Saving and loading environments
* conda env export > env.yaml
* conda env create -f environment.yaml  (to create env from yaml file)

List environments
conda env list
conda env remove -n env_name

Create python ver specific envs
conda create -n py2 python=2 
conda create -n py3 python=3

Sharing env in github
include a pip requirements.txt file using pip freeze (learn more here) for people not using conda.

Conda myths and misconceptions
https://jakevdp.github.io/blog/2016/08/25/conda-myths-and-misconceptions/

https://conda.io/docs/using/index.html


conda env create -f aind-environment-unix.yml

Download the aind-environment-unix.yml file at the bottom of this page (right click, save file).
conda env create -f aind-environment-unix.yml to create the environment.
source activate aind 
